Recommends: xdg-desktop-portal-gnome | xdg-desktop-portal-kde | xdg-desktop-portal-wlr
Suggests: nvidia-driver
Description: Wayland-native NVIDIA streaming for Discord
 Nitrogen is a hardware-accelerated screen capture and streaming tool
 designed for NVIDIA GPUs on Wayland. It captures your screen via
 PipeWire and xdg-desktop-portal, encodes with NVENC, and presents
 as a virtual camera for Discord.
 .
 Features:
  - Hardware-accelerated H.264/HEVC/AV1 encoding
  - Low-latency PipeWire capture
  - Virtual camera output via v4l2loopback
  - Configurable quality presets (720p to 4K)
  - File recording support
